trans-unit.source: Defines the set of exceptions that can be thrown by a .NET script engine.
Exception string: The application domain cannot be set.

Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.GetOption%2A> method or the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.SetOption%2A> method when attempts fail to set the AppDomain option on a managed engine, such as the Visual Basic or JScript script engines.
Managed script engines do not support using custom application domains.
Managed script engines will always use the application domain in which they are running.
To be added.
Exception string: The specified application domain is not valid.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.GetOption%2A> method or <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.SetOption%2A> method when attempting to set an AppDomain reference that is not valid.
To reset the `AppDomain` option to a null reference, call the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.Reset%2A> method.
To be added.
Exception string: Application base cannot be set.

Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.GetOption%2A> method or <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.SetOption%2A> method when attempts to get or set the ApplicationBase option on a managed engine, such as the Visual Basic .NET or JScript .NET script engines.
The host must set the `ApplicationBase` option in the application domain in which it creates its script engine.
To be added.
Exception string: The specified application base directory is not valid.

Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.GetOption%2A> method or <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.SetOption%2A> method when attempts to get or set the ApplicationBase option on an engine, and by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.Run%2A> method when the directory specified as the Application Base directory is not a valid directory.
To be added.
Exception string: <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaReferenceItem> does not reference a valid assembly.

Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.Compile%2A> method when one of the `IVsaReferenceItem` objects contained in the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaItems> collection does not represent a valid assembly.
To be added.
Exception string: Assembly name is not valid.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaReferenceItem.AssemblyName%2A> property when an assembly name that is not valid is specified for a <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaReferenceItem> object.
To be added.
Exception string: Assembly format is not valid.
Thrown when the assembly provided to the engine is not valid.
This exception typically occurs when an engine tries to run or use the assembly.
To be added.
Value: 0x8013303D
Exception string: The specified browser was not found.
Thrown by the aDTEngine.AttachDebugger method when a remote debugging session has been initiated and an attempt made to launch the remote browser, but a browser is not available.
To be added.
Exception string: The cached assembly is not valid.

Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.Run%2A> method when it is called and it tries to use a previously cached assembly, but the assembly is not valid, for example, it is a null reference (`Nothing` in Visual Basic).
To be added.
To be added.
Value: 0x8013304C
Exception string: Cannot attach to the specified Web server.
Thrown by the aDTEngine.AttachDebugger method when launching a server-side debugging session and VSA cannot attach the debugger to the specified Web server.
To be added.
Exception string: A valid Code Document Object Model (CodeDOM) is not available.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaCodeItem.CodeDOM%2A> property when the property is not available to be read.
The engine either does not support the property or it requires an explicit call to the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.Compile%2A> method in order to generate the Document Object Model (DOM).
To be added.
Value: 0x8013300A
To be added.
Value: 0x8013303E
Exception string: Debug target application not started.

Thrown by the aDTEngine.AttachDebugger method when a Windows client debugging session is initiated, but the `AttachDebugger` method is not able to launch the target application that is specified with the TargetEXE option.
To be added.
Value: 0x8013300B
Exception string: The use of debug information is not supported.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.GenerateDebugInfo%2A> property when it is set to true, but the engine does not support the generation of debugging information.
Compilation continues, but the engine compiles code without debug information.
To be added.
Value: 0x8013300C
Exception string: The element name is not valid.

Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaPersistSite.LoadElement%2A> method and <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaPersistSite.SaveElement%2A> methods when either is called with a name parameter that is not valid, for example, one that contains characters that are not valid.
Note that the host must not throw an ElementNameInvalid Exception when the name parameter is a null pointer, as a null pointer is a valid argument used to request engine-level data.
To be added.
Value: 0x8013300D
Exception string: The element was not found.
Thrown by <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaPersistSite.LoadElement%2A> method when it is called with a name parameter that is not valid, that is, one that does not correspond to a previously saved element.
To be added.
Value: 0x8013300E
Exception string: Engine is busy servicing another thread.
Thrown by all members when an engine is currently servicing a request from another thread.
By design, a .NET script engine should only be called from one thread at a time.
To be added.
Value: 0x8013300F
Exception string: The specified engine cannot be closed.
Thrown by <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.Close%2A> method when an attempt is made to call this method, but the.
NET script engine cannot be closed properly.
To be added.
Exception string: The specified engine cannot be reset.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.Reset%2A> method when it is called, but the .NET script engine could not be reset or its events could not be unhooked.
To be added.
Exception string: Engine has been closed.
Thrown in most cases after the .NET script engine has been closed using a call to the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.Close%2A> method.
Once the Close method has been called, the engine can no longer be used, and a new script engine must be created to perform any tasks.
To be added.
Exception string: The specified engine has no source items to compile.

Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.Compile%2A> method when it is called, but there are no items in the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaItems> collection to compile, that is, the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaItems.Count%2A> property = 0.
To be added.
Exception string: Engine has already been initialized.

Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.LoadSourceState%2A> method and <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.InitNew%2A> methods when these methods are called but the .NET script engine has already been initialized.

If the host wants to load source state or initialize a new script engine, the respective methods must be the first ones called after setting the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.RootMoniker%2A> and <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.Site%2A> properties.
To be added.
Exception string: The specified engine name is already in use by another engine.
Thrown by <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.Name%2A> property when an attempt is made to set it to the same name as that of an existing .NET script engine inside the host.
While the Name property does not need to be globally unique, it cannot be the same as the name of a script engine that is currently being hosted.
To be added.
Value: 0x8013303F
Exception string: Engine name not valid.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.Name%2A> property if the specified name is already in use by another engine.
VSA requires that design-time engine names be unique.
To be added.
Value: 0x8013303F
Exception string: Engine name not valid.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.Name%2A> property if the specified name is already in use by another engine.
VSA requires that design-time engine names be unique.
To be added.
To be added.
Exception string: Engine does not exist.
Thrown by the aIDE.ExtensibilityObject property in cases where there are no valid engines from which to retrieve the extensibility object.
To be added.
Exception string: The specified engine has not been initialized.
Thrown by multiple members when the .NET script engine has not been properly initialized, and the host tries to access a property or method that requires the script engine to be initialized.
To be added.
Exception string: The specified engine must be running.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.Reset%2A> method and <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.Assembly%2A> property when either is called and the specified .NET script engine is not running.
To be added.
Exception string: Engine is running.
Thrown by multiple members when the .NET script engine is running, and the host attempts to perform an operation that is not allowed while the script engine is running.
For example, attempting to create a new code item using the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaItems.CreateItem%2A> method will produce this exception if the engine is in the running state.
To be added.
Exception string: The specified event source does not exist.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaSite.GetEventSourceInstance%2A> method when it is called with a parameter or pairing of parameters that is not valid.
Either the `itemName` parameter refers to an item that the host did not add to the engine, or the `eventSourceName` parameter refers to an event source that was not added to the specified item.
To be added.
Value: 0x8013301A
Exception string: The specified event source name is already in use.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaCodeItem.AddEventSource%2A> method when it is called with an `eventSourceName` parameter that has previously been used as an event source name.
To be added.
Value: 0x8013301B
Exception string: The specified event source name is not valid.

Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaCodeItem.AddEventSource%2A> method and <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaCodeItem.RemoveEventSource%2A> methods when either is called with an `eventSourceName` parameter that is not a valid identifier.
Hosts can determine whether an identifier is valid by first calling the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.IsValidIdentifier%2A> method.
To be added.
Value: 0x8013301C
Exception string: The specified event source not found.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaCodeItem.RemoveEventSource%2A> method when it is called with an `eventNameType` parameter that is not already in use as an event source in the code item.
To be added.
Value: 0x8013301D
Exception string: The specified event source type is not valid.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaCodeItem.AddEventSource%2A> method when it is called with an `eventSourceType` parameter that is not a valid type.
Note that this is not true for the Visual Basic script engine, which instead reports a compile exception in this situation.
To be added.
Exception string: File format is not supported.
Reserved for future use.
To be added.
Exception string: File is of unknown type.
Reserved for future use.
To be added.
Value: 0x8013301E
To be added.
Value: 0x8013301F
Exception string: The specified global instance does not exist.

Thrown by <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaSite.GetGlobalInstance%2A> method when it is called with an invalid name parameter, that is, one that was not added using the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaItems.CreateItem%2A> method.
To be added.
Exception string: Global instance type is not valid.
Thrown when the `TypeString` property of an <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaGlobalItem> object is not valid.
To be added.
Exception string: An internal compiler exception has occurred.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.Compile%2A> method when it is called and an unexpected exception occurs within the compiler.
This exception is not thrown for compilation errors, which are signaled to the host by means of the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaSite.OnCompilerError%2A> method, but for exceptions in the compiler itself.
To be added.
Exception string: The specified item cannot be removed.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaItems.Remove%2A> and <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaItems.Remove%2A> methods when an attempt is made to remove an item that cannot be removed.
To be added.
Exception string: The item cannot be renamed.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaItem.Name%2A> property in cases where an attempt is made to rename an item that cannot be renamed.
To be added.
Exception string: The specified flag is not supported.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaItems.CreateItem%2A> method when the call specifies a flag that is not valid, or a flag that is not supported by the host.
To be added.
Exception string: The specified item's name is already in use.

Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaItems.CreateItem%2A> method and the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaItem.Name%2A> property when a call to the `CreateItem` method is made with a name parameter that is already in use, or when an existing item has its `Name` property set to a name that is already in use.
To be added.
Exception string: Item name is not valid.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaItems.Item%2A> property when the name of an item is not valid.
The name of an item can be set either when calling the `CreateItem` method, or when setting the `Name` property.
Use the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.IsValidIdentifier%2A> method to determine whether an identifier is valid for the engine.
To be added.
Exception string: The specified item not found in the collection.

Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaItems.Item%2A> property, <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaItems.Remove%2A> method, <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaItems.Item%2A> property, and <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaItems.Remove%2A> method when the aItems.Item property is indexed using a parameter that is not valid.

When using the string overload, the name parameter must be the same as the name of an item already in the collection; when using the int overload, the `index` parameter must be between 0 and the value of the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaItems.Count%2A> property -1, inclusive.
To be added.
Exception string: The specified item type is not supported.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaItems.CreateItem%2A> method when a call is made with an `itemType` parameter that is not supported by the engine.
Note that not all engines support all the values of the VsaItemType enumeration.
To be added.
Exception string: The specified locale identifier (LCID) is not supported.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.LCID%2A> property when it is set to an LCID that is not supported by the engine.
To be added.
Exception string: The specified element could not be loaded.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.LoadSourceState%2A> method and <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaPersistSite.LoadElement%2A> methods when a call to the `LoadElement` method fails.
The `LoadSourceState` method returns the LoadElementFailed exception from the `IVsaPersistSite.LoadElement` method.
To be added.
Value: 0x8013304A
Exception string: n/a Reserved for future use.
To be added.
Exception string: Missing source.
Reserved for future use.
To be added.
Exception string: The engine name exceeds the allowable length of 256 characters.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.Name%2A> property in cases where the value set for the engine name exceeds 256 characters.
To be added.
Value: 0x8013304B
Exception string: n/a Reserved for future use.
To be added.
Value: 0x8013302A
Exception string: The specified notification is not valid.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaSite.Notify%2A> method when it is called with a notification that is not valid.
It is generally recommended that host applications ignore notifications of which they are not aware, or to which they do not need to respond.
However, in cases where they do handle a specific notification and the notification is not valid, hosts should throw the NotificationInvalid exception.
To be added.
Exception string: The aDTEngine.InitCompleted method has not been called.
Thrown by the aDTEngine.GetIDE method or by the signTime.ShowIDE method in cases where either is called before the `InitCompleted` method has been called, signaling that initialization is complete.
In the case of the `ShowIDE` method, the exception signals that the first engine in the engines collection has not yet been initialized.
To be added.
Value: 0x8013302B
Exception string: The specified option is not valid.

Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.SetOption%2A> method and <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.SetOption%2A> methods when the host attempts to set an option using either method, but the value supplied is not valid for the option.
To be added.
Value: 0x8013302C
Exception string: The specified option is not supported.

Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.SetOption%2A> method <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.SetOption%2A> method, <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.GetOption%2A> method, and `IVsaItem.SetOption` methods when trying to get or set an option that is not supported by the engine
To be added.
Exception string: n/a Reserved for future use.
To be added.
Exception string: n/a Reserved for future use.
To be added.
Value: 0x8013302D
Exception string: A request to revoke the assembly cache failed.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.RevokeCache%2A> method when it is called, but it cannot revoke the cache.
More information may be available by means of the Exception.InnerException property.
Note that if there is no cached assembly to revoke, the engine should return "success" and not throw this exception.
To be added.
Value: 0x8013302E
Exception string: The <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.RootMoniker%2A> property has already been set and cannot be set again.
Thrown by the `IVsaEngine.RootMoniker` property when an attempt is made to set this property after it has already been set to a valid value.
The `RootMoniker` property can only be set once.
To be added.
Value: 0x8013302F
Exception string: The specified root moniker is already in use.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.RootMoniker%2A> property when an attempt is made to set this property to a value that is already in use by another engine.
The `RootMoniker` property must be globally unique.
To be added.
To be added.
Exception string: The <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.RootMoniker%2A> property has not been set.

Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.Compile%2A> method, <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.LoadSourceState%2A> method, <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.Run%2A> method, and <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.InitNew%2A> methods, and the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.Site%2A> property when the property or method requires a valid root moniker, but the `RootMoniker` property has not been set.
To be added.
Exception string: The protocol specified in the root moniker is not valid.

Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.RootMoniker%2A> property when an attempt is made to set this property to a value that uses a protocol already registered on the machine, such as file or http.
Registered protocols cannot be used as part of the moniker.
To be added.
Exception string: The specified root namespace is not valid.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.RootNamespace%2A> property when an attempt is made to set this property to a value that is not a valid namespace identifier.
To be added.
Exception string: The root namespace has not been set.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.Compile%2A> method if it is called before the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.RootNamespace%2A> property is set.
The runtime loader engine and the Visual Basic script engine will also throw this exception on calling the Run method if the property has not been set.
To be added.
To be added.
Exception string: The specified element could not be saved.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.SaveSourceState%2A> method and <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaPersistSite.SaveElement%2A> methods when a call to the `SaveElement` method fails.
The `InnerException` property of the <xref:System.Exception> class is set to the actual exception thrown by the underlying code (for example, an out of disk space exception).
For more information, see <xref:System.Exception.InnerException%2A?displayProperty=fullName>.
The `SaveSourceState` method returns the `SaveElementFailed` exception from the `SaveElement` method back to the caller.
To be added.
Exception string: The specified site has already been set.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.Site%2A> property when an attempt is made to set this property and it already has a non-null value.
Once it has been set, the Site property cannot be reset.
To be added.
Exception string: The specified site is not valid.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.Site%2A> property when an attempt is made to set this property to a value that is not a valid <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaSite> object reference.
To be added.
Exception string: Site has not been set.

Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.Compile%2A> method, <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.LoadSourceState%2A> method, <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.Run%2A> method, and <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.InitNew%2A> methods when a property or method that requires a valid <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaSite> object is called, but the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaEngine.Site%2A> property has not been set.
To be added.
Value: 0x8013303A
Exception string: Source item is not available for this exception.
Thrown when there is no source item for an exception, that is, the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaError.SourceItem%2A> property is not set.
To be added.
Value: 0x8013303B
Exception string: Source moniker is not available for this exception.
Thrown when there is no moniker for an exception, that is, the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaError.SourceMoniker%2A> property is not set.
To be added.
Value: 0x801330FF
Exception string: Unknown exception.
Thrown by multiple members when the exception is not recognized.
To be added.
Value: 0x8013303C
Exception string: Invalid URL; ASPX file extension is missing.
Thrown by the <xref:Microsoft.Vsa.IVsaDTEngine.TargetURL%2A> property when the target URL to which the debugger is set is not valid.
The property must be pointing to an ASPX file.
To be added.
Exception string: n/a Reserved for future use.
To be added.
